The '''Festival of the Three Continents''' ({{lang-fr|Festival des 3 Continents}}) is an annual [[film festival]] held since 1979 in [[Nantes]], France, and is devoted to the cinemas of [[Asian cinema|Asia]], and [[African cinema|Africa]] and [[Latin American cinema|Latin America]]. It was founded by Philippe and Alain Jalladeau.<ref name=DH>[http://www.deccanherald.com/content/Dec302007/finearts2007122943791.asp Deccan Herald] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080725110027/http://www.deccanherald.com/Content/Dec302007/finearts2007122943791.asp |date=2008-07-25 }}, "Films from three continents", Retrieved 12-15-2008</ref><ref>[http://www.whatsonwhen.com/sisp/index.htm?fx=event&event_id=24799 whatsonwhen.com] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718040746/http://www.whatsonwhen.com/sisp/index.htm?fx=event&event_id=24799 |date=2011-07-18 }}, Retrieved 12-15-2008</ref><ref>[http://travelguides.lastminute.com/sisp/index.htm?fx=event&event_id=24799 travelguides.lastminute.com], Retrieved 12-15-2008</ref> The top award in the festival's competition is the balloon shaped Golden [[Hot air balloon|Montgolfiere]].<ref name=DH/> In conjunction with the festival is the Produire au Sud, or Producers of the South, a project that provides funding to independent film productions from Asia, Africa and Latin America.<ref name=DH/>
