{{third-party|date=August 2018}} {{Infobox recurring event | |name= Umatilla County Fair |image=Hermiston fairgrounds.JPG |caption=Fairgrounds located at the end of Orchard St. |location= [[Hermiston, Oregon]] |years_active= 1912 - Present |dates= Aug. 10 - Aug. 14, 2010 |genre= [[County fair]] |website= http://www.co.umatilla.or.us/fair/ }}
The '''Umatilla County Fair''' is a [[fair]] held in [[Hermiston, Oregon|Hermiston]] in [[Umatilla County, Oregon]].<ref name="Fair">{{cite web|title=Umatilla County Fair|url=http://www.co.umatilla.or.us/fair/index.html|website=Umatilla County Fair|publisher=www.co.umatilla.or.us|accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref> The fair runs from the middle of June through to the middle of August each year.<ref name="Schedule">{{cite web|title=Fair Schedule|url=http://www.co.umatilla.or.us/fair/pdf/Fair_schedule.pdf|website=Umatilla County Fair|accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref> Started in August 1912, it was known as the Hermiston Dairy and Hog Show as a joint fair with [[Morrow County, Oregon|Morrow County]], a one time only affair since legislation in 1913 changed it so that it was no longer possible to have a bi-county fair.<ref name="History">{{cite web|title=Umatilla County Fair History|url=http://www.co.umatilla.or.us/fair/fair_history.html|website=Umatilla County Fair|publisher=www.co.umatilla.or.us|accessdate=January 3, 2018}}</ref>
This old fashioned fair is held annually in [[Eastern Oregon]] and generally provides [[traveling carnival|traveling carnival rides]], livestock and open class exhibits, live entertainers with bleacher capacity of about 500 people in conjunction with [[Farm City Pro Rodeo]].<ref name="Schedule" />
